KCNA flails bill on Japanese SDF's overseas dispatch to Iraq 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- The three ruling coalition parties of Japan at the special committee of the House of Representatives on July 3 reportedly railroaded a bill on dispatching the Japanese self-defence forces to Iraq under the pretext of "supporting Iraq in its post-war rehabilitation". The bill will be adopted as a law by the end of this month and the SDF troops will enter Iraq from this fall.
 This provided the Japanese reactionaries with a permanent legal guarantee for dispatching the SDF to any combat areas in the world and launching expansion overseas in real earnest so as to realize their old dream of the "Greater East Asia Co-Prosperity Sphere". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has always worked hard to launch expansion overseas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries have become more undisguised in their moves to provide a legislation for overseas aggression since the beginning of the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In October 2001 Japan adopted the "law on special measure on terrorism" and on may 15 this year it adopted three bills on "emergency", thus legalizing the SDF's participation in any war of overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan increased the SDF's capability for an actual war by sending it to several parts of the world, while laying a framework for its overseas dispatch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In 1992 it sent the SDF to Cambodia under the pretext of protecting election observers and in 1994 to Rwanda and after the September 11 incident to Afghanistan, East Timor and other countries expanding the sphere of its activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In may last the SDF participated in the U.S.-led cobra gold military exercises, the largest-ever in Asia, and in the subsequent period in Japan-U.S. joint military exercises staged in the U.S. with F-15 fighters and early-warning and control plane of its air SDF involved. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The adoption of a bill on dispatching heavily armed ground, maritime and air SDF at the same time to Iraq for the first time in the history of its overseas dispatch shows well to what a dangerous phase Japan has gone in its moves for its troops' overseas dispatch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries' dangerous moves for expansion overseas are bound to go bust due to strong censure and condemnation by the Korean and other Asian people.

Month of anti-U.S. joint struggle marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- A meeting, lecture and photo exhibition took place in Kampala, Uganda, and Champlan, France and by the French Group for the Study of the Juche Idea from June 25 to 29 on the occasion of the month (June 25-July 27) of anti-U.S. joint struggle.
 Chango Machyo, senior advisor to the presidency of Uganda, said at the meeting that the Korean war was a great ordeal to the Korean people, but they defeated the united states and gained a great victory in the war thanks to the outstanding military strategy of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Andre Aubry, representative president of the France-Korea Friendship Association, stated that the victory of the Korean people in the Korean war greatly encouraged the world people in their struggle for independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the French Group for the Study of the Juche Idea said in a lecture that the sovereignty and peace of Korea are guaranteed by the Songun policy of leader Kim Jong Il.

Anniversary of Kim Il Sung's demise commemorated abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Memorial meetings took place in Jordan, Democratic Congo, Romania, Egypt, France and Pakistan from June 30 to July 4 on the occasion of the 9th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's demise.
 Political and public figures of those countries made speeches at the meetings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers said that 9 years have passed and the century changed since Kim Il Sung, the great leader of the Korean people, passed away, but he is always with the Korean people and the progressive people of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung was the greatest man who had devoted his all to the freedom and happiness of the people to the last moments of his life since he embarked on the road of the revolution in his early years, they said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il, the sun of the 21st century, who is identical with Kim Il Sung, the sun of the 20th century, has successfully carried forward his revolutionary cause. And the Korean people will certainly build a great prosperous powerful nation and achieve national reunification, the desire of the nation, under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lectures, seminars and film shows took place in Russia, Bulgaria, Austria, Malaysia, Singapore, Equatorial Guinea and Democratic Congo.

Many foreign decorations awarded to Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung was awarded over 30 orders, medals and prizes and 20 odd honorary titles by different countries and international bodies for the past nine years from July Juche 83 (1994). Among them are highest order, solidarity order, gold medal, medal of honorary citizenship, prize of genius, and titles of honorary academician, professor, doctor and citizenship.
 On July 17, Juche 83 (1994), the organization of socialists in the mediterranean presented its order first class to the president in recognition of his devoted service for the strengthening and development of the socialist movement and global peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The socialist progressive party of Lebanon awarded its specially instituted highest order to him for the first time on the lapse of 100 days after his demise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In Damascus, a meeting took place to name a newly-built street "Kim Il Sung Street" and a decision on awarding an honorary citizenship to the president was issued in April Juche 91 (2002), his 90th birth anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also received Sukarno Order of Indonesia, titles of honorary academician and doctor of the international information technology academy, prize and citation of the permanent office for Afro-Asian writers, title of honorary doctor of pedagogy of Chiclayo University in Peru, gold medal and honorary diploma of the French institute for the fidelity in work, and titles of honorary citizenship, medals and diplomas of honor from ten odd cities of Peru, Ecuador and other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those orders, medals, prizes and honorary titles are diverse and rich in content and they were exceptional in the practice of awarding. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a manifestation of the world people's deep reverence and praise for the president as well as clear evidence of his high international prestige.

Message to Kim Jong Il from Norodom Sihanouk 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il received a message from Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk on July 1 on the occasion of the 9th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's demise.
 The message recalled that by wisely leading the Korean people Kim Il Sung liberated the country and achieved world-startling proud and great successes in economy, social affairs, education, culture, science and technology, industry and all other fields of the country and thus turned the DPRK into an independent and progressive modern state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It noted that the Cambodians and the king himself would always remember the most precious and warm brotherly reception, support and cordial hospitality accorded to him by the president and the multilateral and disinterested aid given by the DPRK to Cambodia in various fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message expressed belief that the heroic Korean people would make new progress in the building of the country and in the cause of achieving the reunification of the Korean peninsula independently and peacefully to glorify his immortal exploits under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message expressed conviction that the excellent ties of friendship, fraternal solidarity and multilateral cooperation between the two peoples would last forever.

Korea, cradle of human civilization 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Archaeologists of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have recently proved that the Korean nation had introduced astronomy in their life from ancient times.
  While studying grooves on the covers of the dolmens, a typical form of tomb in the period of Tangun Korea, archaeologists ascertained in a scientific way that the grooves are the same with constellations at that time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are the great bear, the milky way and comet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sizes of the grooves are different according to the luminance of the stars.  Some grooves linked with each other by lines show what constellations they are. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over 200 of several hundred dolmens with such grooves have been found in Pyongyang and other areas along the River Taedong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dolmens belong to the period from the first half of the 3000s b.c. (4,500-5,000 years ago) to the latter half of the 2000s b.c. (3,000-3,500 years ago).

Undying exploits of Kim Hyong Jik 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- July 10 is the 109th birth anniversary of Kim Hyong Jik, an indomitable revolutionary fighter. With the approach of this anniversary, a large number of people have visited his statues in different parts of the country.
 They look back with deep emotion the immortal feats he performed in the history of the Korean people's anti-Japanese national liberation struggle. He embarked on the road of revolution in his early years and devoted his all to the independence of the country and the happiness of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He convened the historic Pyongyang meeting on March 23, Juche 6 (1917) and formed the Korean national association, the largest underground revolutionary organization in Korea at that time. The anti-Japanese organization embraced Koreans at home and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyong Jik put forward policies of the proletarian revolution, revolutionary armed activities, etc. and rallied broad segments of people in the anti-Japanese struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He advanced the idea of "Jiwon" (aim high) that the liberation of the country should be achieved through struggle continued generation after generation. He, under the motto of "Jiwon", brought up his children to be indomitable revolutionaries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His idea was successfully materialized by President  Kim Il Sung, his eldest son. The president liberated the country and built a powerful socialist state on this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The noble life and exploits of Kim Hyong Jik have always been kept in the memory of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His statues, museums and monuments were built in Kangdong county of Pyongyang, Sakju county of North Phyongan Province, Junggang county of Jagang Province and other places of the country associated with his revolutionary activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Schools, units and places were named after him. Among them are  Kim Hyong Jik University of Education, Kim Hyong Jik Military Medical University, Kim Hyong Jik People's Hospital and  Kim Hyong Jik county. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Feature films including "The Green Pine Tree" and "Dawn" have been released and books published on the basis of his life and activities. 
 "Green Pine Standing on Nam Hill," "Song of Advance" and other songs created by him are still popular among the people.

Drop of "theory of principal enemy" urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- The South Korean military authorities' advocacy of the "theory of principal enemy" is aimed to direct the people's hatred against the U.S. imperialists to the fellow countrymen in the north.
 They should immediately drop this theory, pondering over the consequences to be entailed by its advocacy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson today says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The South Korean military authorities in teaching materials titled "moral education" distributed among frontline units called the government, the army and the citizens in the north "principal enemies". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called their fellow countrymen the "principal enemy" and openly declared confrontation at a time when all Koreans are out in a nationwide struggle for reconciliation and unity, peace and reunification in the idea of "by our nation itself" under the banner of the June 15 Joint Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is an unpardonable challenge to the desire of the fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their advocacy of this theory is intended to serve the purpose of the strategy of the U.S. imperialists to replace the confrontation between the entire Korean nation and the U.S. on the Korean peninsula by that between the two parts of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their vociferation about this theory clearly indicates that they are acting a servant pulling the nuclear war chariot of the U.S. imperialists.

U.S. loudmouthed "naval blockade" against DPRK blasted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Some days ago, Luis, member of the policy advisory committee of the U.S. Defense Department, when interviewed by the Japanese Sankei Shimbun, asserted the need to make naval blockade against the DPRK. He cried out for throwing a network of blockade in waters off Nampho, Anju, Wonsan, Chongjin and others to intercept all its "suspicious ships" and inspect their cargo.
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary dismisses his remarks as part of the U.S. media diatribe aimed to veil the criminal nature of its naval blockade against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No sleight of hand on the part of the U.S. can cover up the criminal nature of its naval blockade, notes the commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to international law and norms governing international relations including the un charter and the convention on the un law of the sea, the commentary holds that the naval blockade against the DPRK is a grave criminal act of infringing upon the sovereignty of an independent state, an unreasonable terrorism in the sea and a gross violation of international law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such brigandish naval blockade of the U.S. is as dangerous an act as igniting a new war on the Korean peninsula, the commentary observes, and continues: paragraph 15 of the Armistice Agreement stipulates that all opposing parties shall not engage in blockade of any kind of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In case the U.S. conducts naval blockade against the DPRK and lays an "international siege" to it, this may soon lead to the total abrogation of the armistice agreement. then there is no need to explain what this means.
